> For beloved apps, Buffalo wings have few rivals. This salad features the dream team—Frank's Hot Sauce + ranch dressing—plus it's a dinner, lunch, or even brunch idea ready in under 30. It wouldn't be Buffalo without a drizzle of Frank's Hot Sauce to finish.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in an even layer and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to cool.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces. Finely dice half the @celery{2.5%ounce}; thinly slice remaining celery on a diagonal. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together half the @buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}, @olive oil{3%tablespoon} (6 TBSP for 4 servings), juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4), and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} until well combined.

In a #large bowl{}, add lettuce, sliced celery, @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}, @croutons{2}, and as much sliced onion and lemony ranch as you like. Toss to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if needed.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @Frank's Seasoning Blend{1/4%ounce}, remaining plain ranch dressing, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings). Stir in minced onion and diced celery.

Once chicken is cool enough to handle, roughly chop. Add to bowl with Buffalo mayo and stir to coat.

Divide salad between bowls. Top with Buffalo chicken and drizzle with @hot sauce{1} to taste.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.